{"title_page": "2020 coronavirus pandemic in Alabama", "text_new": "{{short description|Details of ongoing viral pandemic in Alabama, United States}}\n{{use mdy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox pandemic\n| name            = 2020 coronavirus pandemic in Alabama\n| map1            = \n| legend1         = \n| disease         = [[COVID-19]]\n| virus_strain    = [[SARS-CoV-2]]\n| location        = [[Alabama]], U.S.\n| first_case      = [[Montgomery County, Alabama|Montgomery County]]\n| arrival_date    = March 13, 2020\n| confirmed_cases = 5,296<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://alabamapublichealth.gov/covid19/index.html|title=Alabama Department of Public Health (ADPH)}}</ref>\n| deaths          = 181 - expanded case definition <br/> 144 - confirmed\n| hospitalized_cases = 699 (cumulative)\n| critical_cases  = \n| ventilator_cases = \n| website         = [http://alabamapublichealth.gov/covid19/index.html Alabama Department of Public Health]\n}}\n\nThe [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]] was confirmed to have reached the U.S. state of [[Alabama]] in March 2020. As of April 21, 2020, the Alabama Department of Public Health reported 5,296 cases of COVID-19 and 144 confirmed deaths. The state reports a total of 181 deaths within the CDC's expanded case definition.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.alabamapublichealth.gov/infectiousdiseases/2019-coronavirus.html|title=Coronavirus Disease 2019 (COVID-19) {{!}} Alabama Department of Public Health (ADPH)|website=Alabama Department of Public Health|access-date=April 16, 2020}}</ref><ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.wsfa.com/2020/03/17/adph-update-public-covid-am/|title=Alabama coronavirus cases climb to 39; Closures ordered in some counties|author=WSFA Staff|website=WSFA|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-17}}</ref>\n\n== Timeline ==\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic data/United States/Alabama medical cases chart}}\n{{Bar chart\n| float       = right\n| title         = New Cases Reported Per Day in Alabama\n| ca